# Joseph as chief administrator of Egypt — national famine-management plan.
# Phase artifact: family-arrival (domain fragment). Joseph's family arrives and is received and provisioned (exception path).
# One admitted PDDL Turtle planning artifact; fragments across all phase
# artifacts merge structurally into ONE combined plan (domain name
# 'joseph-famine' shared by every fragment). Formal planning-to-workflow
# demonstration domain; argues no doctrine, claims no historicity.
@prefix ex: <http://example.org/joseph#> .
@prefix ceng: <urn:chatman:engine#> .

ex:josephs-brothers ex:arrive ex:egypt .
ex:jacobs-household ex:receives ex:provision .

ex:family-arrival ceng:pddlDomain """
(define (domain joseph-famine)
  (:requirements :strips)
  (:predicates
    (foreign-buyers-supplied ?x)
    (family-received ?x)
    (family-provisioned ?x))
  (:action receive-family
    :parameters (?x)
    :precondition (and (foreign-buyers-supplied ?x))
    :effect (and (family-received ?x)))
  (:action provision-family
    :parameters (?x)
    :precondition (and (family-received ?x))
    :effect (and (family-provisioned ?x))))
""" .
